-Mj0P66ZJfhaHl9-_8kS.text: Edina police officers have been searching in and around Rosland Park for Iklas Abdullahi Ahmed, a 2-and-a-half-year-old girl who went missing yesterday evening at around 5 p.m.

-Mj0PP1LtvuF2wnF8Jbm.text: She was last seen wearing a yellow top, blue leggings, pink shoes, and an orange hijab. She is reported to be autistic and nonverbal, and she may not respond.

-Mj0PTCsB2EEgR5LxmgX.text: Police believe the girl may have wandered away from family on her own yesterday evening.

-Mj0Q7NPL-FanOX2yebF.text: Edina PD advise residents to stay away from the park but to check the areas surrounding the park for the girl. According to a press release by the City of Edina, the search effort continued throughout the night last night, and the search is ongoing.
